England soccer manager Roy Hodgson
gave Southampton striker Jay Rodriguez a first call-up to the
national squad for games against Chile and  Germany .  Fellow Saints Adam Lallana and Rickie Lambert are also
selected after their club started the season strongly, standing
sixth in the Premier League after 10 games.  The exhibition matches are at Wembley on Nov. 15 and Nov.
19. The Football Association announced the squad  on its website .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
